records.addlTxt:
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 2, obstruct officer.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 1.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for twelve (12) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Maintain absolute sobriety;
3) Send letter of apology to each officer involved in this incident;
4) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
5) Spend thirty (30) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
The defendant is entitled to one day credit if revoked.
$250.00 cash bail is ordered applied to court costs.
Minutes.
